	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64833277">You don't need that level of integration. HAFAS, the company creating it more than 25 years ago, did the work. They asked all the public transport companies for their schedules, put them in a large database, published an API for the companies to do updates of their own schedules, and then created a path finding algorithm along all those different schedules.
<p>
25 years ago, you could go to HAFAS' website, enter two points of interest somewhere in the vicinity of at least one of the public transport providers,<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

